            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Begin with honest evaluation of your existing roof: Roof age - How old is your current roof? (Critical information—most materials have predictable lifespans). Visible problems - Active leaks, missing or damaged materials, obvious wear? Repair history - Frequency and cost of repairs over past 5 years. Energy performance - High cooling costs suggesting poor insulation or solar heat gain? Aesthetic concerns - Appearance matching or updating home's architecture? Future plans - How long will you own the home? Solar panel installation planned? Document current issues with photos and notes. Consider whether repair or replacement makes better economic sense using this guideline: If repair costs exceed 40-50% of replacement cost, or roof age exceeds 75% of expected lifespan, replacement typically provides better value. Schedule professional inspection ($200-400) for expert assessment if significant problems exist or purchase/sale is imminent."
