            "content": "Understanding Manufacturer Material Warranties: All roofing materials include manufacturer warranties covering defects, but understanding coverage details is critical. Typical warranty terms: Architectural shingles: 25-50 years (depending on product tier), with coverage often prorated after 10-15 years meaning you pay proportional cost for defective materials. Tile roofing: 50 years to lifetime for premium products; concrete tile typically 50 years, clay tile often lifetime. Metal roofing: 30-50 years depending on finish and material; paint/finish warranties typically 30-40 years. Flat roof membranes: 15-30 years depending on product; TPO and EPDM typically 20-25 years. Important warranty limitations: Coverage limited to material defects (not installation errors, storm damage, or normal wear), often require annual professional inspections with documentation, may be voided by unauthorized repairs or modifications, and typically don't cover labor costs (only replacement materials). Transferability: Most manufacturer warranties are transferable to new homeowners with proper registration, adding significant value when selling. We ensure proper warranty registration within required timeframes (typically 60-90 days after installation), maintain required documentation, and explain all coverage terms clearly."
